        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:25:1",
        "relations": null,
        "text": [
          " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) تَخَتَّمُوا بِالْجَزْعِ الْيَمَانِيِّ فَإِنَّهُ يَرُدُّ كَيْدَ مَرَدَةِ الشَّيَاطِينِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Ubeyd Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn Bin Ali Bin Al Husayn, from his father, from his grandfather who said, ",
            "‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘You should be wearing rings with the Yemeni onyx for it repels the plots of the Accursed satans<sup>la</sup>’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘Abd Allah from Muhammad ibn Ali from ‘Ubayd ibn Yahya from Muhammad ibn al-Husayn ibn Ali ibn al-Husayn from his father from his grandfather has said the following: “’Amir al-Mu’minin, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Use Yemenite carnelian as the ring; it dispels plots, the evil plans of defiant Satans.’” "
          ]
        }
